## Correctness Verification

For each major document, verify claims against the actual code:

| Document | Claim | Code Evidence | Match? |
|---|---|---|---|
| `README.md` | "Supports Python 3.9+" | `pyproject.toml: python = ">=3.9"` | ✅ |
| `docs/setup.md` | "Run `make build`" | `Makefile: build target exists` | ✅ |
| `docs/api.md` | "GET /users returns paginated results" | `routes/users.js: pagination implemented` | ✅ |
| `README.md` | "Test coverage > 90%" | Coverage report: 72% | ❌ |

## Gaps Analysis
| Gap | Type | Impact | Effort to Fix |
|---|---|---|---|
| Missing deployment runbook | Missing | Operations cannot self-serve | M |
| Outdated architecture diagram | Incorrect | Misleads new developers | S |
| No API documentation | Missing | API consumers blocked | L |

